# StoneRise Marketing Messaging Rules

All marketing ad copy must align with the Positioning & Messaging Canvas. Reference doc: `Marketing/stonerise-positioning-messaging-canvas.md`

## Brand Asset (Logo)

- Use the official StoneRise logo from `Marketing/Brand/stonerise-logo.png` in any marketing creative where a logo is needed
- Do not recolour, distort, stretch, or add effects to the logo
- Keep clear space around the logo (no tight cropping)

## Target Audience

- **Company:** UK construction sub-contractors and main contractors
- **Persona:** Procurement, Commercial & Financial Teams at **Manager/Director level** — including Procurement Manager, Procurement Director, Head of Procurement
- **Use Case:** Purchasing materials, managing external suppliers, consolidating spending

## Category Framing

Always position StoneRise as **"Construction Procurement Software"** — never generic "SaaS", "ERP" or "business software".

## Messaging Hierarchy (follow this order)

1. **Lead with the problem** — fragmented, manual procurement causing overspend, delays, errors
2. **Introduce the category** — construction procurement software
3. **State the solution** — one digital workflow for the entire procurement process
4. **Reinforce with pillars** — multi-supplier management, automated POs, rule-based approvals, real-time tracking
5. **Prove with benefits/stats** — use the approved proof points below
6. **Close with differentiation** — better prices, faster approvals, fewer problems on site

## Four Differentiation Pillars

Always frame capabilities around these four pillars:

| Pillar | Core Message |
|--------|-------------|
| Centralised Multi-Supplier Management | Compare quotes from multiple suppliers instantly |
| Automated PO Creation | Auto-build POs from approved requests with specs attached |
| Rule-Based Approvals | Custom approval chains with escalation logic and mobile access |
| Real-Time Order Tracking | Live status, delivery photos, audit trails |

## Approved Proof Points

Use these stats in copy — do not invent new ones:

- Invoices processed in **3 minutes**
- **20%** time saved per order
- **90%** fewer admin errors
- Approval delays reduced by **75%**
- **90%** fewer delivery disputes

## Approved Core Copy Blocks

**One-sentence description:**
> StoneRise is an automated procurement tool that helps Commercial & Financial teams in construction purchase materials, manage external suppliers and consolidate spending in one digital workflow.

**Differentiation summary (use as CTA foundation):**
> Better prices, faster approvals and fewer problems on site.

**Problem hook:**
> Construction firms use a fragmented, manual process for procurement that results in overspend, poor supplier visibility, compliance gaps and costly delays.

## Four Sub-Problems (use in hooks and pain-point copy)

1. Overspend & pricing inconsistencies from manual, disparate systems
2. Admin overload, errors and invoice disputes from paperwork and manual POs
3. Slow, inconsistent approvals vulnerable to bottlenecks
4. Zero visibility on requests and deliveries causing delays and compliance failures

## Tone & Voice

- Speak to professionals — confident, direct, no jargon-for-jargon's sake
- Use construction-industry language naturally (POs, RFQs, site, subcontractors, quantities)
- Problem-first, solution-second — always lead with the pain
- Quantify outcomes wherever possible
- Never use "revolutionary", "game-changing" or generic SaaS hype language

## Do NOT

- Call StoneRise an "ERP", "platform" or "suite" in ad copy — use "procurement software" or "procurement tool"
- Invent statistics not listed in approved proof points
- Use generic benefits — always tie back to construction-specific outcomes
- Ignore the messaging hierarchy — problem first, always
